<br>
I'd swing my sword in the blink of an eye, I'd wave my arms for spellcasting in half a second, the shimmering animation of the water was more like a frenetic spasming. It was all very disorienting. The worst part was that the animation of me (and also monsters) running would move so fast that I was constantly lag ghosting. Unfortunately the consequences of my actions weren't speeded up (even though the animation of my swordswing was over in the blink of an eye, I didn't actually swing any more often than usual).<br>
<br>
If I would have been hasted as fast as the animations were..., it would have been tempting to cause some merry havoc. I'm not into exploits, but I would have had to tear something up with my 700% haste, just for fun, lol. Fortunately, that temptation didn't occur.<br>
